  <EntryCount>65</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Though the wind and the ice have pried long, jagged cracks in the walls, the doors feel as solid - and as cold - as a glacier. 

Gilded panels are arranged in columns along the doors. Though most depict scenes from daily life - dwarves chiseling at tunnel walls, hauling minecarts, or feasting at long tables - one pane at eye level catches your attention.

It's a relief showing a crenelated wall and, above it, an indentation in the shape of an anvil.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>The gilded panel shows an image of a crenelated wall and an iron anvil that you socketed into place.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hammers of Durgan, ring loud! May the anvil's deep music resound."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Examine the relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the door.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Distantly, you hear the melodic chime of metal on metal and the low chorus of a work song.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Walls of the Battery safeguard our works from marauder and wilder alike."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Abydon's faithful travail by the Forge and the fires that brighten the ore."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>Nothing happens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Strike the anvil relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the crenelated wall relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Strike the crenelated wall relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave it for now.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>The thrum of essence dissipates into the brisk mountain air.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>Peering closer, you notice that the anvil-shaped impression is strangely dull and smooth, as if hasn't been exposed to the elements for long. 

You suspect that something may have filled it until recently.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>Even with all of your weight behind it, it doesn't budge.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>The buzz of essence fades, and the relief reverts to its original state.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you do, a single, ringing tone whistles through the air. Your hand buzzes and vibrates like struck metal.

When you look back at the relief, the panels on either side of the wall and anvil have come alive. Ogres and warriors of all races gather for battle, their shapes and silhouettes formed by flaring, whorled heat patterns.

The tiny figures move and dance, animated by the flicker and blaze of an unseen fire.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>It doesn't move.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Strike the warriors.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Walls of the Battery safeguard our works from marauder and wilder alike."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Abydon's faithful travail by the Forge and the fires that brighten the ore."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>The hot metal burns your hand. The warriors continue their martial dance.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>Nothing happens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>You hear the heavy thud of some kind of mechanism loosening behind the plaque.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the crenelated wall relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Press the panel.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>The panel cools and returns to its original state.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>The gilded panel now feels pleasantly warm, but it doesn't move.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>It slides easily with the slightest pressure from your fingers. You guide it up and over the anvil relief, where it clicks into place.

Beneath it is a deep cavity. It's shaped like a dragon's gaping jaws.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Abydon's faithful travail by the Forge and the fires that brighten the ore."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Stick your finger into the cavity.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>Warm air gusts from the open mouth, tingling your cold-numbed face.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>You take one finger and stick it into the mouth of the sculpture, probing the space behind it. You pull your hand back, only to see...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Use your torch to light a fire in the mouth.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Use your head to light a fire in the mouth.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Examine the mouth more closely.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Stick your weapon into the mouth.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hammers of Durgan, ring loud! May the anvil's deep music resound."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>The heat billowing from the mouth prevents you from getting too close, but the rim of the cavity - and the tiny teeth surrounding it - are blackened with soot. 

You accidentally inhale some of the vapor. It's odorless, but it leaves you light-headed.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>You poke at the edge of the mouth, but nothing happens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>Nothing happens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fire catches the warm vapor with a billowing whoosh. The dragon's eyes are alight, and flames lick at the edges of its mouth. 

A few seconds later, the panel is sliding away from you as the two enormous doors swing open into a grand hall.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Place the anvil tile in the relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>The anvil-shaped tile fits perfectly in the impression. You feel a warm thrum in your fingertips as you snap it into place.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Examine the relief.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>This panel isn't as bright or detailed as the others, but it's a masterwork of precision - every ridge and groove is straight and even.

The relief is pitted from centuries of exposure, yet the metal feels warmish to your hands.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave it for now.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the door.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>Even with all of your weight behind it, it doesn't budge.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>Peering closer, you notice that the anvil-shaped impression is strangely dull and smooth, as if hasn't been exposed to the elements for long. 

Judging by the depth of the impression, you suspect that it's a socket for a tile or relief of some kind.

Furthermore, you see well-worn grooves alongside the anvil socket.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>Peering closer, you notice that the anvil-shaped impression is strangely dull and smooth, as if hasn't been exposed to the elements for long. 

Judging by the depth of the impression, you suspect that it's a socket for a tile or relief of some kind.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>This panel isn't as bright or detailed as the others, but it's a masterwork of precision - every ridge and groove is straight and even.

In fact, you notice well-worn grooves running alongside the anvil pane.

The relief is pitted from centuries of exposure, yet the metal feels warmish to your hands.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hammers of Durgan, ring loud! May the anvil's deep music resound."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Push the door.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText>Even with all of your weight behind it, it doesn't budge.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>...a layer of soot covering your finger.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>72</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Stick your finger into the cavity.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>You reach toward the open mouth but draw back as the heat stings your hand.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Use flint and tinder to light a fire in the mouth.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hammers of Durgan, ring loud! May the anvil's deep music resound."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>You also notice that the dragon's "tongue" is a fire striker. It's hinged and attached to a chunk of flint.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Press the dragon's tongue to light a fire in the mouth.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
